# Plaud Export Skill

Export Plaud Note Pro recordings (transcripts + summaries) to Google Drive.

## Quick Command

```bash
node ~/clawd/scripts/plaud-export.js
```

## What It Does

1. Fetches files from the **ToExport** folder on web.plaud.ai
2. Downloads transcripts (with speaker ID + timestamps) and AI summaries
3. Saves to Google Drive:
   - Summaries ‚Üí `Plaud Inbox/`
   - Transcripts ‚Üí `Plaud Inbox/Raw Transcripts/`

## Output Format

```
2026-01-26 1330 - Meeting Title - Summary.md
2026-01-26 1330 - Meeting Title - Transcript.md
```

## CLI Options

```bash
node ~/clawd/scripts/plaud-export.js                    # Export ToExport folder (default)
node ~/clawd/scripts/plaud-export.js --list-folders     # List all folders
node ~/clawd/scripts/plaud-export.js --folder <id>      # Export specific folder
node ~/clawd/scripts/plaud-export.js --unfiled          # Export unfiled recordings
```

## Token Refresh

If the script fails with auth errors, the token expired (~1 year lifespan). Refresh:

1. Go to web.plaud.ai, open console (Cmd+Option+J)
2. Run: `localStorage.getItem('tokenstr')`
3. Save: `echo 'bearer eyJ...' > ~/.plaud-token`

## After Export

Remind Dave to move exported files from **ToExport** to **Processed** folder in Plaud web UI.

## Source

GitHub: https://github.com/benchuser00/plaud-export (private)
Local: ~/code/plaud-export/
